@startuml
title Docs frontend — Rocket launch lifecycle

' Five-phase finite-state sequence per rocket launch animation spec.
' Transitions are time-based against the simulation clock (FIXED_STEP = 1/60 s)
' so the sequence is deterministic across machines and refresh rates.

[*] --> Idle : page loaded

Idle    : FAB hidden or compact\n(no canvas, no transform)
Armed   : FAB pill expanded\nrocket icon brightened
Boil    : 0 to PRE_MS (2 000 ms)\nthick volumetric smoke\naround the launch pad
Flight  : 0 to DURATION (2 600 ms)\nrocket follows fixed Bezier path\nsmoke killed at lift-off
Cleanup : up to one frame\ncanvas removed,\nGPU resources freed

Idle    --> Armed   : reader within arming\ndistance of footer
Armed   --> Idle    : reader scrolled away
Armed   --> Boil    : click on FAB\n(reduced motion = no-preference)
Armed   --> Idle    : click on FAB\n(reduced motion = reduce)\nscroll-to-top instant
Boil    --> Flight  : simTs >= PRE_MS\nsmoke killed,\nsmooth scroll dispatched
Flight  --> Cleanup : simTs >= PRE_MS + DURATION\n— or — safety-net 5 000 ms
Cleanup --> Idle    : onDone fires,\nisLaunching = false

note right of Boil
  determinism contract:
  - fixed RNG seed (0x51F15EED)
  - fixed timestep 1/60 s
  - identical visual on every click
end note

note right of Flight
  emission off in default config
  (EMIT_SMOKE_IN_FLIGHT = false)
  smoke does not follow the rocket
end note

@enduml
